# Main recipe for creation
200 g of couvetyre chocolate in pellet form
2 dl of coffee

Prepare coffee
Prepare tin cans
Melt chocolate in pan on medium temperature.
Pour coffee into melted chocolate in very small batches. 
Pour also a little of "thick coffee" with a lot of grounds in it.
Stir during pouring and inbetween pourings.
Pour chocolate with mixed-in coffee into small tin cans.
Pat on top of poured cholate to even it out in the can. Be careful to not push it out to the edges of the tin can.

